## Quick Reference Commands

```bash
# Web Development
cd web
npm install
npm run dev          # Start dev server
npm run build        # Production build
npm run lint         # Check lint
npm run lint:fix     # Fix lint errors
npm test             # Run tests

# API Development
cd api
npm install
npm run start:dev    # Start dev server
npm run build        # Production build
npm run test         # Run tests

# Haystack Development
cd haystack
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # or `venv\Scripts\activate` on Windows
pip install -r requirements.txt
python main.py       # Start server (port 8000)

# Git Workflow
git checkout develop
git pull origin develop
git pull origin master  # Sync develop with master first
git checkout -b feature/my-feature
# ... changes ...
npm run build  # ALWAYS verify build
git add .
git commit -m "feat: Description\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>"
git push -u origin feature/my-feature
# STOP - Wait for user approval
git checkout develop
git merge feature/my-feature --no-ff
git push origin develop
```

---

**Remember**: When in doubt, ask the user for clarification. It's better to ask than to make incorrect assumptions about requirements or architecture.
